Redox reactions between metal oxides of different valence states can also be used for TCES. The first task in developing the TCS system based on the redox reaction is to find suitable metal oxides. Wong B used the HSC chemical reaction and equilibrium software to calculate the equilibrium thermodynamics of 74 different pure metal oxides, in which nominal air (79% N2 and 21% O2) at atmospheric pressure was used as the carrier gas [241]. This work screened some important redox systems, as shown in Table 12.Table 12
